r goes in the intersecting region.<p>While not technically a Venn Diagram I think it is still a useful graphic.</p></p></p></p></div></div></div><div class="comment"><div class="commentnumber">2</div><div class="commenthead">30 points by <a class="userlink" rel="Qz">Qz</a> 4  days ago <a title="number and link to replies to this comment" href="http://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=2048373">3 replies</a> <span  title="expand this comment" class="commentopener">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><div class='text'>This article takes something simple and elegant (if incorrectly labeled) and turns it into a sad tortured example of how to get yourself picked on in high school.</div></div></div><div class="comment"><div class="commentnumber">3</div><div class="commenthead">26 points by <a class="userlink" rel="panacea">panacea</a> 4  days ago <a title="number and link to replies to this comment" href="http://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=2048393">1 reply</a> <span  title="expand this comment" class="commentopener">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><div class='text'>He's right though. Line diagrams as JPEGs <i>are</i> annoying.</div></div></div><div class="comment"><div class="commentnumber">4</div><div class="commenthead">4 points by <a class="userlink" rel="Bud">Bud</a> 4  days ago <a title="number and link to replies to this comment" href="http://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=2049359">0 replies</a> <span  title="expand this comment" class="commentopener">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><div class='text'>I laughed out loud at the bit about "probably something from Bruce Schneier". Really funny stuff overall. If you didn't like this, you need to relax and have more egg nog.</div></div></div><div class="comment"><div class="commentnumber">5</div><div class="commenthead">7 points by <a class="userlink" rel="jaekwon">jaekwon</a> 4  days ago <a title="number and link to replies to this comment" href="http://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=2048235">2 replies</a> <span  title